r mental nature of language structure, the areal factor in lexical typology and the diachronic implications of semantic maps. The collection will thus be of relevance to typologists and historical linguists, as well as to people studying variation within the areas of cognitive and functional linguistics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCognitive grammar. 0aGrammar, Comparative and general. 0aTypology (Linguistics) 0aTypology (Linguistics). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDiachrony.  aTypology.  aVariation.1 aBrisard, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrisard, Frank, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDivjak, Dagmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGast, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaspelmath, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIdiatov, Dmitry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoptjevskaja-Tamm, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKönig, Ekkehard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLarrivée, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoeschler, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMortelmans, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMortelmans, Tanja, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOlmen, Daniël, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocab